Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of East Greek pottery oinochoe; exterior: glazed black (fired brown); inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 100 (= Well 2) [almost certainly]
Curator's comments: Almost certainly from same jug as 1886,0401.491, which was found in Well 100 (no.2)

Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.431)
